ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Good introduction to some useful methods for modeling the kinematics of robots. I would recommend it to someone who could use the material.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Overall was pretty helpful content for robotics students.

The course covers very important basic robotics, the DH parameters and the Jacobian. The course covers these topics systematically and thoroughly. Other aspects of robot design such as "design for mathematical simplicity" are also explained in detail, this is essential for any practical robot design.
